COMMUNICATION: How to talk to other players and staff

IN-ROOM (everyone in your current room hears these)
  say <message>        Speak, subject to the language system.
  ooc <message>        Speak out-of-character. Skips the language
                        system -- everyone in the room understands --
                        and is tagged (ooc). Room-local only: there
                        is no global OOC channel anywhere in the game.
  shout <message>      Speak loudly. Skips the language system.
                        5-second cooldown between shouts.
  whisper <who> <msg>  Private in-room message; only the named player
                        hears it, everyone else sees that you
                        whispered to someone.
  emote <action>       Perform an action (visible to room).
  converse             Auto-say mode; everything you type is spoken.
                        Type ** to exit converse mode.

CROSS-ROOM
  radio <message>        Broadcast on your radio's tuned frequency
                          (see: radio). Requires a carried radio
                          item. Only other radios on the same
                          frequency hear you.
  telepathy <who> <msg>  Psionic mind contact. Requires the telepathy
                          psionic power, ISP, and both players
                          online. Requires introduction first (see:
                          introduce). Not available to characters
                          without psionic ability.

STAFF CONTACT
  tell <staff> <msg>  Send a private message to online wizard staff.
                      Mortals cannot tell other mortals; use
                      telepathy after introducing yourself instead.
  reply <msg>         Reply to the last tell you received.

INTRODUCTION SYSTEM
  introduce <player>  Introduce yourself to a player in the same
                      room. Both parties learn each other's names.
                      Required before telepathy can target another
                      player.

WIZARD STAFF ONLY
  wiz <message>  Broadcast to every online wizard regardless of
                 room. Restricted to staff; mortals cannot use it.

NOTES
  There is no global OOC channel and no other player-facing chat
  channels of any kind (no newbie/guild/gossip lines, no channel
  toggles). Radio and telepathy are the only two ways to reach
  someone who is not in your room.
  shout is available to players; yell is not (staff only).
  Type 'help <command>' for details on any specific command.

SEE ALSO: say, whisper, shout, telepathy, radio, tell, ooc, introduce,
channels
